The White House press briefing on February 22, 2012 covered a range of topics including Syria, gas prices, tax reform, and Iran. Press Secretary Jay Carney expressed condolences for two journalists who were killed in Syria and reiterated the need for international action to pressure Assad to relinquish power. He also discussed the President's commitment to lowering gas prices through increased domestic oil and gas production, as well as investing in alternative energy sources. On tax reform, Carney highlighted the President's proposal to lower corporate tax rates and eliminate subsidies and loopholes. He also addressed concerns about the administration's use of the Espionage Act and its impact on press freedom. Finally, Carney commented on the IAEA's unsuccessful trip to Iran and the need for Iran to abide by its international obligations.